Friedrich Donenfeld[1] (17 January 1912 – 20 March 1976) was an Austrian footballer and football manager.

He played for Thalia Wien, Hakoah Wien, Maccabi Tel Aviv, Olympique de Marseille and Red Star Saint-Ouen.

He coached the Colombia national football team,[2] Junior Barranquilla,[3][4] the Netherlands national football team, Fortuna '54,[5] DHC,[6] Enschedese Boys,[7] DOS Utrecht,[8] FC Twente, MVV[9] and PEC Zwolle, among others.
